<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10659707>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. Rhagovelia mimani n. sp., male, dorsal and ventral habitus views with major morphological structures as used in this work labelled; specimen from Papua New Guinea, Central Prov., Dorobisoro. Dorsal view, An1–An4 = antennal segments I–IV; Eye = eye; Vt = vertex; PrN = pronotum; MsN = mesonotum; MtN = metanotum; Cnx = connexiva; AT1–AT8 = abdominal tergites I–VIII; Pr = proctiger; FF = fore femur; FT = fore tibia; MF = middle femur; MT = middle tibia; Mts1–3 = middle tarsal segments I–III; HF = hind femur; HT = hind tibia. Ventral view, G = gula; R = rostrum; PP = propleura; PS = prosternum; Pac = proacetabula; MsS = mesosternum; MP = mesopleuron; MsAc = mesoacetabula; MtS = metasternum; MtAc = metacetabula; AV1–9 = abdominal ventrites I–IX; FTr = fore trochanter; FTs3= fore tarsal segment III; MCx = middle coxa; MTr = middle trochanter; HCx = hind coxa; HTr = hind trochanter; HTs1–3 = hind tarsal segments I–III." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10659707/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10659709>
    dc:description "FIG. 3. Rhagovelia mimani n. sp., female, dorsal and ventral habitus views with major morphological structures as used in this work labelled; specimen from Papua New Guinea, Central Prov., Dorobisoro. Dorsal view, An = antenna; Eye = eye; Vt = vertex; PrN = pronotum; MsN = mesonotum; MtN = metanotum; Cnx = connexiva; AT1–AT8 = abdominal tergites I–VIII; Pr = proctiger; FF = fore femur; FT = fore tibia; MF = middle femur; MT = middle tibia; HF = hind femur; HT = hind tibia. Ventral view, G = gula; R = rostrum; PP = propleura; PS = prosternum; Pac = proacetabula; MsS = mesosternum; MP = mesopleuron; MsAc = mesoacetabula; MtS = metasternum; MtAc = metacetabula; AV1–8 = abdominal ventrites I–VIII; FTr = fore trochanter; FTs3= fore tarsal segment III; MCx = middle coxa; MTr = middle trochanter; Mts1–3 = middle tarsal segments I–III; HCx = hind coxa; HTr = hind trochanter; HTs1–3 = hind tarsal segments I–III." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10659709/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10659713>
    dc:description "FIGS. 4, 5. Rhagovelia dibuwa n. sp., male genitalic structures, with specific characters as discussed in text labelled. 4. Proctiger. 5. Intact male genitalic complex, right lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10659713/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10659715>
    dc:description "FIGS. 6–9. Rhagovelia species females from the EPCT region, dorsal views of fully winged morphs showing shapes of wings and expansion of pronotum. 6. R. suloga n. sp., specimen from Woodlark Island, CL 7217. 7. R. aviavi n. sp., specimen from Lakekamu River basin, New Guinea, CL 7156. 8. R. kolukolu n. sp., specimen from Tagula Island, CL 7194. 9. R. mimani n.sp., specimen from Dorobisoro, New Guinea, CL 7263." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10659715/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10659763>
    dc:description "FIGS. 85–90. Rhagovelia watuti n. sp., structural details; specimens from New Guinea, Cloudy Mountains, CL 7175. 85. Wingless male, dorsal habitus. 86. Wingless female, dorsal habitus. 87. Male right hind leg, posterior view. 88. Male right hind leg, dorsal view. 89. Male left paramere, outer lateral view. 90. Male proctiger, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10659763/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10659771>
    dc:description "FIG. 98. Goilayoli River headwaters, east of Alotau, Milne Bay Province, Papua New Guinea, CL 7161, habitat for R. peninsularis n. sp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10659771/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10659801>
    dc:description "FIG. 145. Tributary to the upper Mimani River, near Dorobisoro, Central Province, Papua New Guinea, CL 7262, habitat for R. peggiae Kirkaldy, R. mimani n. sp., and R. loriae n. sp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10659801/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10659834>
    dc:description "FIGS. 194–199. Rhagovelia mimani n. sp., structural details; specimensfrom New Guinea, Mimani River basin, nearDorobisoro. 194. Wingless male, dorsal habitus; specimen from Mimani River tributary, CL 7262. 195. Wingless female, dorsal habitus. 196. Male right hind leg, posterior view. 197. Male right hind leg, dorsal view; 195–197 from Mimani River tributary, CL 7263. 198. Male left paramere, outer lateral view. 199. Male proctiger, dorsal view; 198 and 199 from Mimani River tributary, CL 7259." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10659834/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10659838>
    dc:description "FIG. 201. Distributions in eastern New Guinea of species held as Incertae Sedis within the R. novacaledonica group in regard to subgroup assignments." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10659838/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

